election_record.label: Massachusetts 1816 Lieutenant Governor

sub_unit.name: Clarksburg
sub_unit.note: The votes from Clarksburg were rejected.

sub_unit.name: Windsor
sub_unit.note: There were no votes recorded in Windsor for Lieutenant Governor, though there were votes for Governor.

sub_unit.name: Holland
sub_unit.note: The votes from Holland were rejected.

sub_unit.name: South Hadley
sub_unit.note: The votes from South Hadley were rejected.

sub_unit.name: Appleton Plantation
sub_unit.note: There were no votes recorded in Appleton Plantation.

sub_unit.name: Concord
sub_unit.note: William Phillips received 1 vote as William Philliam.

sub_unit.name: Dracut
sub_unit.note: William Phillips received 1 vote as William Philliam.

sub_unit.name: Dunstable
sub_unit.note: William King received 1 vote as William King rather than Honorable William King.

sub_unit.name: Mendon
sub_unit.note: The Annals of the Town of Mendon, 498, lists 43 votes for William Phillips in Mendon.
